g.text: 1st Battalion left Italy for UK via Sicily with 231 Brigade.
1st Battalion and 231st Brigade sailed from Syracuse in the ‘Durban’ for UK as part of 50th Division.
1st Bn (231 Bde), 50 (Northumberland) Div, embarked for ‘Overlord’ (invasion of Normandy) and sailed on the evening of 5th June.
1st Bn enlarged 50 Div bridgehead by clearing Asnelles, Arromanches and Manvieux.

Invasion D Day. 1st Bn (231 Bde) landed at Le Hamel and Les Roquettes as right assault Bn of 50 Div and British 2nd Army, and encountered stiff opposition at Le Hamel. The third assault landing made by the Bn in 11 months.
1st Bn (231 Bde) in Battle for Hottot.
7th Battalion suffered severe casualties in the Battle for Maltot.
1st Battalion (231 Brigade) suffered severe casualties in the Second Battle for Hottot.
1st Battalion and 231 Brigade withdrawn from the Line to rest at Les Fietees.
1st Battalion, right Battalion of 231 Brigade, in 50 Divisional attack towards Villers Bocage.
7th Battalion in battle for Cahagnes.
1st Battalion in break-out battles from Bridgehead to Villers Bocage.
7th Battalion in Battle for Mount Pincon.
1st Battalion at St Pierre La Vielle.
7th Battalion at St Denis de Mere.
1st Battalion advanced with 11th Armoured Division through Argentan – Vernon – Amiens to Arras. Advance ended 2nd September.
7th Battalion move to River Seine.
7th Battalion at crossing of River Seine at Vernon.
7th Battalion at Tilley.
1st Battalion completed advance with 11th Armoured Division through Argentan – Vernon – Amiens to Arras.
1st Battalion advanced with Guards Division in record advance from Arras to Brussels (97 miles in 14 hours). 1st Battalion first to enter Brussels.
1st Battalion and 231 Brigade re-joined 50th Division SE of Antwerp.
1st Battalion enter Antwerp with 11th Armoured Division.
1st Battalion advance through Albert Canal bridgehead to Escault Canal.
7th Battalion enter Brussels.
1st Battalion in break out from Escault Canal into Holland.
1st Battalion advanced up the right flank of the corridor to Nijmegen. The advance ended on 10th October.
7th Battalion at Nijmegen.
7th Battalion move up to Arnhem.
7th Battalion in relief of 1st Airborne Division.
7th Battalion in Battle of Randwyk.
7th Battalion in the Battle for the Factory.
1st Battalion crossed the River Waal at Nijmegen.
7th Battalion in the Brosbeek – Mook Sector.
1st Battalion in the Battle of Bemmel.
7th Battalion move to Bergendal.
1st Battalion in the operations in the ‘Island’ between Nijmegen and Arnhem.
1st Battalion (50th Division) in operations in the ‘Island’ between Nijmegen and Arnhem.
7th Battalion engaged at Osbsbeek.
7th Battalion took over the Line at Gilraith.
7th Battalion minefield incident at Panhandle Wood.
1st Battalion withdrawn from the line in 50th Division and concentrated at Ypres.
7th Battalion moved to Harselt/Celles area.
7th Battalion in action in Brunsum area.
7th Battalion secure bridges at Celles Huy Seraing against Ardennes offensive.
7th Battalion move to Meerssen.
7th Bn moved to concentration area at Teveren.
7th Bn takes Waldenrath and Putt.
7th Bn moved to Dremmen and Porselen.
7th Bn in action Metterath.
7th Bn in action at Treebeck.
7th Bn concentrated to prepare for Reichswald Battle.
7th Bn move to Helmond.
7th Bn moved to assembly area, Nijmegen.
7th Bn in Bedberg – Berkofel Battle.
7th Bn on Millingen Islands.
7th Bn at Kellen opposite Emmerich.
7th Bn at Aaier on River Maas, in preparation for Rhine Crossing.
7th Bn at crossing of Rhine near Rees.
7th Bn at Battle of Millingen.
7th Bn in Battle of Meglechen.
7th Bn at Battle of the Bridges near Anhalt.
7th Bn at Sindereh.
7th Bn in liberation of Hengelo.
7th Bn at Battle of Cloppenburg.
7th Bn in clearing operations around Heiderugg.
7th Bn advances SE Bremen.
7th Bn advance towards Bremerhaven.
